      "content": "No, there is no consensus among economists that tax cuts for the top tier will reliably boost overall economic growth; studies consistently show the evidence is mixed and often weak. While some theorists argue that higher rates discourage saving and investment, the majority of recent research suggests that the tax cuts primarily redistribute wealth downward without generating significant aggregate demand or productivity gains. Ultimately, the economic impact depends heavily on whether the savings are reinvested productively or simply hoarded, a distinction that most empirical data fails to confirm in practice.",
